The Vice President of the United States expressed excitement about the JW Marriott Hanoi, a symbol of the enduring relationship between the US and Vietnam. The structure, which is on a 99-year lease, will serve as a home and facility for important activities, such as Vietnamese students applying for visas to study in the US and meetings on trade and cooperation. The Vice President thanked the leaders of Vietnam for their cooperation and partnership. In response to a question about the Havana Syndrome attacks, the Vice President expressed gratitude to embassy staff for their dedication and sacrifices, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic, and acknowledged their role in representing the best of the United States in its global partnerships.